<TITLE> Lower court judges postpone deadline for Awal's removal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 3 (bdnews24.com) - The lower court judges have postponed for two weeks the 10-day deadline they had given the government to remove acting law secretary Kazi Habibul Awal. Judge Md. Shajahan Saju, the secretary general of the Bangladesh Judicial Service Association, told bdnews24.com Tuesday that an urgent meeting a day before had taken the decision in the wake of the bloody BDR mutiny. Steps would be taken for Awal's removal in the next meeting, he added. They offered prayers for the slain BDR members. bd
